    "description":  "Integrate your data directly with our systems by using Business Gateway. Direct integration saves time, reduces errors and allows you to use a single system. ",
    "details":  {
                    "attachments":  [

                                    ],
                    "body":  "\u003cdiv class=\"govspeak\"\u003e\u003ch2 id=\"tailor-your-experience-with-hm-land-registry-by-connecting-directly-using-business-gateway\"\u003eTailor your experience with HM Land Registry by connecting directly, using Business Gateway\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eDigital applications are now the default route for business customers. There are two different ways to submit your applications online, either through the portal or using legal software through our Business Gateway (API) channel.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch3 id=\"the-portal\"\u003eThe portal\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eIf you do not already use a case-management system (CMS) and have no requirement to streamline or automate processes, then you can submit applications on our online portal, using the \u003ca href=\"https://www.gov.uk/guidance/digital-registration-service\" class=\"govuk-link\"\u003eDigital Registration Service\u003c/a\u003e. The portal is free to use and provides a single platform where you can lodge and monitor applications, reply to requisitions on your own or your colleagues’ behalf, and access information services.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch3 id=\"business-gateway\"\u003eBusiness Gateway\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eBusiness Gateway is an IT solution which allows direct integration between your business and HM Land Registry systems for managing our processes, including submitting digital applications. You can streamline your work and tailor how you work with us to fit neatly into your existing processes – including using client information already in your case management system to quickly compile applications.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch2 id=\"benefits-of-business-gateway\"\u003eBenefits of Business Gateway\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eIntegrate your data directly to HM Land Registry’s systems by using Business Gateway, which can bring a range of potential additional benefits that could better suit your business. Depending on which of our services are connected, direct integration could save time, reduce errors and allow you to work from a single system.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe potential benefits of Business Gateway include:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n  \u003cli\u003epre-populated data - reducing re-typing and human error, automatically pulling through information already entered elsewhere and from the register\u003c/li\u003e\n  \u003cli\u003edata validation and guidance - cutting requisition errors and cancellations by checking against the register as you go, calculating fees and prompting you to upload relevant documents\u003c/li\u003e\n  \u003cli\u003ecollaborating with colleagues  - easily save draft applications, share work and link into other parts of your firm’s process\u003c/li\u003e\n  \u003cli\u003edashboards with reminders and alerts - to view application status, manage by priority and ensure nothing gets missed\u003c/li\u003e\n  \u003cli\u003eautomatic document storage  - never mislay anything and save time downloading and storing documents, with new responses such as registration completed documents automatically collected\u003c/li\u003e\n  \u003cli\u003eeasily reply to requisitions - reply to requisitions through free format notepad or uploading additional documents\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003ch3 id=\"linking-to-other-systems-and-information\"\u003eLinking to other systems and information\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThis means you could access wider benefits such as the ability to:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n  \u003cli\u003eorder searches and keep them in a single platform, including local authority, environmental, mining and more\u003c/li\u003e\n  \u003cli\u003emake all government submissions in one place\u003c/li\u003e\n  \u003cli\u003ehave a single login to all your conveyancing services\u003c/li\u003e\n  \u003cli\u003eaccess streamlined conveyancing workflows, to help with compliance, save time and reduce risk\u003c/li\u003e\n  \u003cli\u003eaccess the latest digital legal forms and editable letters available in one place\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003ch2 id=\"how-to-access-business-gateway\"\u003eHow to access Business Gateway\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThere are two different ways to set up Business Gateway:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch3 id=\"third-party-access\"\u003eThird party access\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eLots of third party suppliers who have developed software that allows access to Business Gateway through a shared CMS platform. The majority of our customers access Business Gateway this way. Not all third party platforms can be customised specifically to your business needs, but still provide direct integration for most core HM Land Registry processes. This route to access Business Gateway is usually preferred by businesses with no IT development resource. If you already have a CMS, the provider might already have Business Gateway integration capability.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eYou can \u003ca href=\"https://www.gov.uk/guidance/third-party-access-to-business-gateway\" class=\"govuk-link\"\u003efind out more about third party access\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch3 id=\"direct-access\"\u003eDirect access\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eDirect access to Business Gateway means when your business links its own existing system, or creates a new system that integrates directly with Business Gateway. This access route is often most suitable for companies that have a designated IT resource with development capability. It can be customised specifically to your business needs, creating a bespoke direct access platform.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eYou can \u003ca href=\"https://www.gov.uk/guidance/direct-integration-with-business-gateway\" class=\"govuk-link\"\u003efind out more about direct access\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e",
